# wg-split shellcheck config. These scripts are busybox-ash for OpenWrt and use
# patterns shellcheck flags but that are correct here; disable only those, so real
# bugs (unquoted expansions, SC2086, etc.) still fail CI.
#
# SC1091  can't follow `. /lib/functions.sh` / common.sh (not present in CI)
# SC2034  "unused" constants — common.sh is a sourced library; sbin scripts use them
# SC3043  `local` — undefined in strict POSIX, but busybox ash supports it
# SC2015  `A && B || C` — intentional terse idiom throughout
# SC2018  tr 'A-Z'  — ASCII-only config text, ranges are deliberate
# SC2019  tr 'a-z'  — ditto
# SC2153  VPN_IFACE/LAN_IFACE "misspelling" false positives
# SC2154  vars assigned indirectly by OpenWrt's config_get
disable=SC1091,SC2034,SC3043,SC2015,SC2018,SC2019,SC2153,SC2154
